Teheran (AFP), 12th.An Iranian official said that a mosque in the southern city of Shiraz was bombed today resulting in the deaths of nine people and over one hundred injured. This is the first bomb in the city center of a non-border Iranian city.Attack event.Fars News Agency quoted the local official as saying that this powerful bombing, that happened at nine in the evening in the male section of the mosque, happened while a well known local Muslim cleric was holding an evening prayer session.The report quoted a hospital representative saying: "This bombing in Shiraz resulted in the injuries of 105 people and nine deaths." All of the city's medical resources have already been redirected to rescuing the victims.The report said that since many of the injured are in serious condition, the death toll will increase.